import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main(){

  runApp(
    Center(
      child: Text(
        "Hello Flutter",
        textDirection: TextDirection.ltr,
      ),
    ),
  );
}

1Ô∏è‚É£ Import Statement
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';


Imports Flutter‚Äôs Material library.

Provides basic widgets like Text, Center, and core Flutter functionality.

2Ô∏è‚É£ main() Function
void main(){


Entry point of the Flutter application.

Execution starts from here.

3Ô∏è‚É£ runApp()
runApp(


Launches the Flutter app.

Takes one widget as its argument.

This widget becomes the root widget of the UI.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Center Widget
Center(


A layout widget.

Centers its child horizontally and vertically on the screen.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Text Widget
child: Text(
  "Hello Flutter",


Displays the text "Hello Flutter" on the screen.

6Ô∏è‚É£ textDirection
textDirection: TextDirection.ltr,


Specifies Left-To-Right text direction.

Required here because:

You are not using MaterialApp

There is no Directionality widget

Without this line, the app will throw an error.

